# Scale & Utility Tokens

## Base Scale (`--scale-*`)

`--scale-*` is the **only numeric primitive token** in the design system. Spacing has been merged into it — there are no separate `--space-*` tokens. Use `--scale-*` for spacing, sizing, dimensions, and all numeric measurements. All values are in `px`.

### Negative values

| Token | Value |
|-------|-------|
| `--scale-n16` | -16px |
| `--scale-n12` | -12px |
| `--scale-n8` | -8px |
| `--scale-n4` | -4px |
| `--scale-n2` | -2px |
| `--scale-n1` | -1px |

